{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Runners A and B are nearing the end of a race. The last portion of track before the finish line is straight. Both runners are moving at a constant speed of 5 m/s. When runner A is 50 m behind runner B, she starts to accelerate at a constant rate of "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"0.25 \text{ m/s}^2 "}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"text","text":"

"},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"At this moment, runner B, still going a constant speed, is 100 m from the finish line"}]},{"type":"text","text":"

"},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Part a) Who wins the race?"}]}]}
